# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
# Prevents accidental commits of sensitive files (API keys in .env.local),
# generated build output, and OS/editor noise. The *.local rule below is the
# critical one — it ensures .env.local (which holds your TMDB API key) is
# never committed, even with a blanket `git add .`.

# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
